section.section:
After the Department receives the permit application, the Department shall prepare a tentative determination, which shall include the following information:
A proposal to issue or to not issue a permit;
Any proposed permit limitations and conditions;
A brief explanation of the Department's tentative determination; and
Any proposed schedule of compliance.

The Department shall prepare a final determination if:
Written comments adverse to the tentative determination were received by the Department within 30 days after the publication of the notice of tentative determination pursuant to this section;
Comments adverse to the tentative determination were received in writing at, or within 5 days after, the public hearing conducted pursuant to this section;
Comments adverse to the tentative determination were received orally at the public hearing conducted pursuant to this section and the Department prepared a transcript of the comments made at the hearing; or
The final determination is substantively different from the tentative determination and all persons aggrieved by the final determination have not waived, in writing, their right to request a contested case hearing.
